  "prompt": "Are there legal requirements for reporting suspected money laundering?",
  "response": "Yes, there are legal requirements for reporting suspected money laundering in many countries. Financial institutions, businesses, and professionals in certain industries are typically required to:\n\n1. Establish customer identification procedures\n2. Monitor transactions for suspicious activity\n3. File suspicious activity reports (SARs) with relevant authorities\n4. Maintain records of transactions\n5. Train employees to recognize potential money laundering indicators\n\nSpecific requirements vary by jurisdiction, but most countries have anti-money laundering (AML) regulations.",
